//!
//! # Defense-in-depth (cross-ref the Envoy SecurityPolicy)
//!
//! The Envoy Gateway `SecurityPolicy` (gateway.envoyproxy.io/v1alpha1) validates
//! the inbound `authorization: Bearer <jwt>` header at the EDGE, before the
//! request reaches this backend. This tower `Layer` re-validates the JWT at the
//! application boundary as a second, in-process check (issuer / audience / JWKS
//! signature) so a request that bypasses the gateway (e.g. in-cluster S2S, or a
//! misconfigured route) is still rejected. The S2S Connect client
//! (`transport_connect_client.rs.tmpl`) presents the Zitadel machine-user Bearer
//! token this middleware validates.
//!
//! # Crate (CARRY-3, verified LIVE 2026-06-04 — evidence.md P-39)
//!
//! Uses `jwt-authorizer = "0.15"` — "jwt authorizer middleware for axum and
//! tonic" (a JWKS-based axum tower layer). The family pin `0.15` is confirmed
//! live; add to this crate's `Cargo.toml.tmpl` when wiring:
//!
//!     jwt-authorizer = "0.15"
//!
//! # Zitadel identity (cross-ref identity.yaml@1.1.0)
//!
//! The JWKS source is the Zitadel discovery endpoint
//! (`https://<zitadel-issuer>/oauth/v2/keys`, CARRY-2 / evidence.md P-38). The
//! issuer is the `zitadel.configmapConfig.ExternalDomain` from the b8-7
//! `values-forge` overlay. identity.yaml@1.1.0 pins: chart 10.0.2, appVersion
//! v4.14.0, ghcr.io.
//!
//! # Hexagonal preservation (Article VII)
//!
//! This is an inbound infrastructure concern (a tower layer), not a domain rule.

